Tell HN: All Heroku Enterprise renewals are getting a 5% price raise
text:
I just got this email from Salesforce this morning:

Your Salesforce subscription for COMPANY will be expiring on 4/28/2023. At the time of renewal, a 5% increase will be applied to your license fees. This incremental increase supports continued investments in our products, infrastructure and services, allowing us to add hundreds of new features, increase datacenter capacity, make our systems more secure and reliable, and other service improvements that benefit our customers.

If you’d like to make any changes or discuss in more detail, please contact me directly at least 30 days prior to the contract end date 4/28/2023.

We look forward to our continued partnership.

Ask HN: Do declining/ed prog langs have more unreasonableness and rudeness?
text:
I won't say which ecosystem, but they dismiss contributions and "other" people not in their routine clique. And if you refuse to bend over to their unprofessionalism, "You're a bad person. If you continue, I will become more self-righteous and ban you. There, I banned you." agro abruptly without saying anything. Doesn't exactly encourage participation.

Is this common amongst languages no one uses or languages that are past their prime?
